        <p id="part1" class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-4">
            Soap is needed to make laundry detergent at home. The molecular structure of soap is divided into pro- and lipophilic parts. <br />
            The lipophilic part can penetrate into the oil, so soap has a strong ability to remove oil.
            Step 1:<br />
            First we prepare a soap head, cut it into thin slices, try to cut it as small and thin as possible, so that it will dissolve better in a while.<br />
            Step 2:<br />
            Prepare a basin or box and pour clean water into it, add baking soda and a little fragrance. Baking soda has a strong ability to remove oil and stains.
            Fragrance can act as a perfume in laundry detergent and remove odors from clothes.<br />
            Step 3:<br />
            Generally, after a few minutes of soaking, the soap will become soft. At this time, the homemade laundry detergent is ready to use. If you want the soap to dissolve completely in water, it is best to leave it overnight.

        </p>

